    <div class="container mt-5">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead text-justify">
            At Jodi Junction, we are committed to safeguarding your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and share your data, ensuring transparency in how we protect your privacy.
        </p>

        <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
        <p>
            Jodi Junction is a matchmaking platform. To provide our services effectively, we collect personal information from you. By using our platform, you consent to the collection, use, and sharing of your personal data as described in this policy.
        </p>

        <h4>We collect three types of information:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Information you voluntarily provide</li>
            <li>Information automatically collected</li>
            <li>Information from third-party sources</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>i. Information You Provide</h4>
        <p>We collect the following personal information when you use our platform:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Registration Data:</strong> Name, gender, date of birth, contact details, educational qualifications, employment information, photos, marital status, and sensitive data like identity proofs.</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Data:</strong> For paid services, you may be required to provide payment information, including bank account details, UPI ID, and debit/credit card information.</li>
            <li><strong>Testimonials:</strong> Data provided when submitting success stories, photos, or feedback.</li>
            <li><strong>Surveys and Promotions:</strong> Information you voluntarily submit while participating in surveys, events, or contests.</li>
            <li><strong>Customer Service:</strong> Information you share when communicating with our customer service team for support and issue resolution.</li>
            <li><strong>Chat and Messages:</strong> Conversations exchanged between you and other users on the platform.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>ii. Automatically Collected Information</h4>
        <p>
            We collect certain information automatically when you use our platform, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Data about the device you use to access our platform (e.g., IP address, browser type, operating system).</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Information collected via cookies to enhance your user experience and improve our services.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>iii. Information from Third-Party Sources</h4>
        <p>
            We may receive information from third-party sources such as social media platforms if you choose to connect your Jodi Junction account with such services.
        </p>

        <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
        <p>
            The personal information we collect is used for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Providing matchmaking services</li>
            <li>Facilitating payments for paid services</li>
            <li>Communicating with you regarding account management, support, and promotional offers</li>
            <li>Improving and personalizing the user experience on our platform</li>
            <li>Ensuring the security and integrity of our platform</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h3>
        <p>
            We do not sell your personal information. However, we may share your data in the following circumstances:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>With other users:</strong> To facilitate the matchmaking process, certain personal information may be shared with other users on the platform.</li>
            <li><strong>With service providers:</strong> We may share your data with third-party service providers to deliver and improve our services (e.g., payment processors, hosting services).</li>
            <li><strong>For legal reasons:</strong> If required by law or in good faith, we may disclose your information to comply with legal obligations or to protect the rights and safety of Jodi Junction, our users, or others.</li>
        </ul>

